    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Big-Omega Notation Demonstration</title>\n    <style>\n        body { font-family: monospace; }\n        .control { margin: 10px; }\n        .output { margin: 10px; }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Big-Omega Notation Interactive Demo</h1>\n<p>Big-Omega (Ω) notation provides an asymptotic lower bound for a function. Explore various functions and their Omega notations here.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n    <h2>Function Type</h2>\n    <button onclick=\"selectFunction('constant')\">Constant (Ω(1))</button>\n    <button onclick=\"selectFunction('linear')\">Linear (Ω(n))</button>\n    <button onclick=\"selectFunction('quadratic')\">Quadratic (Ω(n^2))</button>\n    <button onclick=\"selectFunction('logarithmic')\">Logarithmic (Ω(log n))</button>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"control\" id=\"functionInputs\">\n    <h2>Input Size (n)</h2>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"inputSize\" value=\"1\" min=\"1\" onchange=\"updateOutput()\">\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n    <h2>Execution Time (T(n))</h2>\n    <button onclick=\"calculate()\">Calculate Execution Time</button>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"output\">\n    <h2>Output</h2>\n    <p id=\"selectedFunction\">Selected Function: None</p>\n    <p id=\"executionTime\">Execution Time (T(n)): None</p>\n    <p id=\"omegaNotation\">Omega Notation: None</p>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n    let selectedFunction = '';\n    let n = 1;\n\n    function selectFunction(funcType) {\n        selectedFunction = funcType;\n        document.getElementById('selectedFunction').innerText = 'Selected Function: ' + funcType;\n        updateOutput();\n    }\n\n    function updateOutput() {\n        n = parseInt(document.getElementById('inputSize').value);\n        calculate();\n    }\n\n    function calculate() {\n        if (selectedFunction === 'constant') {\n            executionTime = 1;\n            omegaNotation = 'Ω(1)';\n        } else if (selectedFunction === 'linear') {\n            executionTime = n;\n            omegaNotation = 'Ω(n)';\n        } else if (selectedFunction === 'quadratic') {\n            executionTime = n * n;\n            omegaNotation = 'Ω(n^2)';\n        } else if (selectedFunction === 'logarithmic') {\n            executionTime = Math.log(n); // base e\n            omegaNotation = 'Ω(log n)';\n        } else {\n            executionTime = 'N/A';\n            omegaNotation = 'N/A';\n        }\n        \n        document.getElementById('executionTime').innerText = 'Execution Time (T(n)): ' + executionTime;\n        document.getElementById('omegaNotation').innerText = 'Omega Notation: ' + omegaNotation;\n    }\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
